    <note>Zhang(1) Yaozuo [321] Uncle of Zhao(1) Renzong's [9004] consort, Zhang(1) Guifei [3153]. His younger brother, Yaofeng [13963], and son, Shanfu(2) [13964], are both listed as Yongan (modern Gongxian) residents, which is the location of the imperial tombs and probably none are actually Yongan residents. Perhaps the other Shanfu(3) [17732], a Yanshi resident and chronologically logical, was the same person as Yaozuo's son, who may have been an adopted son, since he was the #2 son of Rushi [11666]. XCB, 147.2a-2b, 160.1b, 161.1a, 166.2a, 14a, 167.7b, 169.13a, 13b, 188.3b; SS, 463.22a. CBD, 3, 2411.</note>
